Yobe State executive council has approved N6,067,305,786.91 for the upgrade of Yobe International Cargo Airport. The state commissioner of information, Alhaji Mala Musti disclosed this to newsmen shortly after executive council meeting was presided over by Governor Ibrahim Gaidam in Damaturu, on Wednesday. Musti said the funds approved will be use to upgrade design and bill of quantity for the completion of the International Cargo Airport. Also approved, according to the commissioner, was N127,187,270.00 to cater for operational expenses of 2019 Hajj. “This is in a bid to meet the deadline of May 30, 2019 for the final remittances of 2019 Hajj fares by the states pilgrims agencies, boards and commissions in Nigeria to NAHCON” he added Yobe approves N3.4bn for security, agriculture, others Yobe expends N784.3m on health, education, Others Yobe okays N8.7bn for roads, drainages Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin